---
import BlogPostLayout from '../../../../layouts/BlogPostLayout.astro';

const lang = 'en-us';
const post = {
  title: 'Atrani',
  subtitle: "Italy's Smallest Village Where Time Stood Still",
  category: 'DISCOVERIES',
  date: 'April 22, 2026',
  readTime: '6 min',
  image: '/images/atrani-hero.jpg',
  imageAlt: "Atrani - Italy's smallest village on the Amalfi Coast",
  path: '/en-us/blog/atrani/',
};

const metaTitle = "Atrani: Italy's Smallest Village on the Amalfi Coast | Guide 2026";
const metaDescription = "Guide to Atrani, Italy's smallest municipality: history of the Doges of the Republic of Amalfi, the Masaniello legend, Netflix's Ripley filming location and practical tips for visiting.";

const breadcrumbs = [
  { name: 'Home', url: '/en-us/' },
  { name: 'Blog', url: '/en-us/blog/' },
  { name: 'Atrani', url: '/en-us/blog/atrani/' },
];

const quickInfo = [
  { label: 'Record', value: "Italy's smallest municipality (0.12 km²)" },
  { label: 'Distance from Amalfi', value: '700 m · 10-15 min walk' },
  { label: 'Access', value: 'On foot from Amalfi · SITA Bus' },
  { label: 'Parking', value: 'Almost none — use Amalfi' },
  { label: 'Cult event', value: 'Feast of St. Mary Magdalene (July 22)' },
  { label: 'Local dish', value: 'Sarchiapone' },
  { label: 'Film set', value: "Ripley (Netflix, 2024)" },
  { label: 'Atmosphere', value: 'Authentic, medieval, peaceful' },
];

const faq = [
  {
    q: 'How far is Atrani from Amalfi?',
    a: 'They are only 700 meters apart. You can walk between them in about 10-15 minutes through the pedestrian tunnel or along the coastal road.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is it difficult to park in Atrani?',
    a: 'Yes, parking is extremely limited and reserved almost exclusively for residents. It is strongly advised to park in Amalfi (Luna Rossa car park) and walk to Atrani.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Is Atrani suitable for a quiet holiday?',
    a: 'Absolutely. Compared to Amalfi or Positano, Atrani offers much slower and quieter rhythms, while still being a step away from the main transport connections of the Coast.',
  },
  {
    q: 'Why was Atrani chosen as the set for Ripley?',
    a: "The Netflix series Ripley (2024) chose Atrani for its ability to evoke a time-suspended Italy, with its arches over the main road, medieval alleyways and a square just meters from the sea. The village has remained almost unchanged compared to decades ago — extremely rare on the Coast.",
  },
  {
    q: "What is Atrani's Sarchiapone?",
    a: "It is the local culinary specialty, traditionally prepared for the feast of Saint Mary Magdalene on July 22nd: a long zucchini stuffed with meat, cheeses and eggs, then fried and baked in the oven. A traditional peasant dish of the coastal area.",
  },
  {
    q: "What is the 'birecto' and why is it linked to Atrani?",
    a: "The birecto was the ducal headwear of the Doges of the Maritime Republic of Amalfi. In Atrani, at the Church of San Salvatore de' Birecto, the solemn investiture of the Doges took place: the village was the center of aristocratic power of the Republic, not the more touristic Amalfi.",
  },
];

const sidebarLinks = [
  { label: 'Discover Amalfi', href: '/en-us/amalfi-coast/amalfi/' },
  { label: 'SITA Bus', href: '/en-us/guide/sita-bus/' },
  { label: 'When to visit', href: '/en-us/when-to-visit/' },
  { label: 'Getting here', href: '/en-us/getting-here/' },
];

const authorRole = 'Amalfi Coast Specialist';

const relatedArticles = [
  {
    title: 'Emerald Grotto',
    category: 'DISCOVERIES',
    date: 'April 22, 2026',
    image: '/images/grotta-smeraldo-hero.webp',
    imageAlt: 'Emerald Grotto - Conca dei Marini, Amalfi Coast',
    path: '/en-us/blog/emerald-grotto/'
  },
  {
    title: 'Ferriere Valley',
    category: 'DISCOVERIES',
    date: 'April 22, 2026',
    image: '/images/valle-ferriere-hero.jpg',
    imageAlt: 'Waterfall in the Ferriere Valley, Amalfi - Amalfi Coast',
    path: '/en-us/blog/ferriere-valley/'
  }
];
---

<BlogPostLayout
  lang={lang}
  post={post}
  metaTitle={metaTitle}
  metaDescription={metaDescription}
  breadcrumbs={breadcrumbs}
  quickInfo={quickInfo}
  faq={faq}
  sidebarLinks={sidebarLinks}
  authorRole={authorRole}
  relatedArticles={relatedArticles}
>

  <!-- Intro -->
  <div>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-xl leading-relaxed mb-6 font-light">
      Just a few steps from the famous and crowded Amalfi, separated only by a short rocky headland, lies Atrani. At just 0.12 km², it is Italy's smallest municipality, but what it lacks in size it more than makes up for in charm, history and authenticity. Atrani is not just a village: it is a natural amphitheater overlooking the sea, a labyrinth of "scalinatielle" (little staircases) and a haven for those seeking the most genuine Amalfi Coast.
    </p>
  </div>

  <!-- Architecture -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">Architecture Fit for Cinema</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      The moment you arrive in Atrani, your eye is caught by the famous arches that support the SS163 coastal road, turning passing traffic into a scenic element that frames the beach and village below. Atrani has kept its medieval structure intact: a tangle of narrow alleys, overlapping white houses and small courtyards that open up unexpectedly, making it one of the <strong>Most Beautiful Villages in Italy</strong>.
    </p>

    <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm">
      <h3 class="font-serif text-xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-4">The Set of Ripley</h3>
      <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed">
        It is no coincidence that Atrani was chosen as the set for <strong>Netflix's Ripley (2024)</strong>, thanks to its ability to evoke a time-suspended atmosphere, far from mass tourism. The alleys, the square and the arches over the main road have remained almost identical to decades ago — an absolute rarity on the Coast.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- History -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">History and Legends: The Heart of the Republic</h2>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-6">
      Despite its proximity to Amalfi, Atrani has always had a strong, aristocratic identity. In the ducal era, this was where the noblest families lived and where, in the <strong>Church of San Salvatore de' Birecto</strong>, the solemn investiture of the Doges of the Maritime Republic of Amalfi took place, with the placement of the "birecto" (the ducal headwear).
    </p>
    <p class="text-slate-600 text-lg leading-relaxed mb-8">
      One of the most fascinating legends concerns the <strong>Cave of Masaniello</strong>: it is said that the famous Neapolitan revolutionary, whose mother was from Atrani, took refuge here among the village's alleyways to escape the viceroy's guards.
    </p>

    <blockquote class="border-l-4 border-med-gold pl-6 my-8">
      <p class="text-slate-700 text-xl font-serif italic leading-relaxed">
        "Atrani is a secret whispered among the rocks, a place where the breath of the sea reaches into the very houses."
      </p>
    </blockquote>
  </div>

  <!-- What to see -->
  <div>
    <h2 class="font-serif text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 mb-6">What to See in Atrani</h2>
    <div class="space-y-4">
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex gap-5">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-med-gold/10 flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-med-gold font-bold text-sm">1</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Piazza Umberto I</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">The beating heart of the village. A small, intimate square just meters from the sand, perfect for a coffee or aperitivo surrounded by the daily life of residents. No souvenir shops, no queues: just authentic Atrani.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex gap-5">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-med-gold/10 flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-med-gold font-bold text-sm">2</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Collegiate Church of Santa Maria Maddalena</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">With its majolica dome dominating the village's skyline, it is one of the most photographed points on the Coast. The baroque facade and position overlooking the sea make it unique.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-[2rem] border border-slate-100 shadow-sm flex gap-5">
        <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-med-gold/10 flex-shrink-0 flex items-center justify-center text-med-gold font-bold text-sm">3</div>
        <div>
          <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">The "Scalinatielle"</h4>
          <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Get lost among the staircases climbing toward the upper part of the village. Every step offers a new view, between laundry drying in the sun and the scent of local cooking. The real Atrani lives here, not on the main road.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <!-- Local Tips -->
  <div class="bg-white p-8 rounded-[2rem] shadow-xl border border-slate-100">
    <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
      <svg class="w-6 h-6 text-med-gold flex-shrink-0" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.5" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M9 18h6"/><path d="M10 22h4"/><path d="M15.09 14c.18-.98.65-1.74 1.41-2.5A4.65 4.65 0 0 0 18 8 6 6 0 0 0 6 8c0 1 .23 2.23 1.5 3.5A4.61 4.61 0 0 1 8.91 14"/></svg>
      <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-slate-900">Expert Tips</h3>
    </div>
    <div class="space-y-6">
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">Arrive on foot from Amalfi</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Instead of taking the bus or car, walk the footpath that starts from the upper part of Amalfi. In less than 15 minutes of panoramic walking you will find yourself in the heart of Atrani, avoiding the traffic on the coastal road.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">The Beach</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Atrani's beach is small and sheltered, ideal for families with children or anyone who wants to enjoy the sun in a more intimate setting compared to nearby Amalfi. Less crowded, more peaceful.</p>
      </div>
      <div>
        <p class="font-bold text-slate-900 mb-1">The Local Dish: Sarchiapone</p>
        <p class="text-slate-600 text-sm leading-relaxed">Don't leave without trying the Sarchiapone, a local specialty traditionally made for Santa Maria Maddalena (July 22nd): a long zucchini stuffed with meat, cheeses and eggs, then fried and baked in the oven.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

</BlogPostLayout>
